# Feature Flag System Decision

## Quick Assessment

| Criterion | Build It | LaunchDarkly | Unleash |
|-----------|----------|--------------|---------|
| Time to ship | ~2 weeks | ~2 hours | ~1 day |
| Ongoing maintenance | High | None | Medium |
| Cost (est.) | Dev time only | $100-400/mo | Hosting ~$20/mo |
| Targeting rules | You build it | Excellent | Good |
| Real-time updates | You build it | Yes | Yes |
| Audit log | You build it | Yes | Yes |
| TypeScript SDK | You build it | ✅ Official | ✅ Official |

---

## My Recommendation: **Unleash**

Here's why, for your specific stack:

```
Team of 4 + Vercel + Render + Postgres =
  - Don't waste 2 weeks reinventing this
  - LaunchDarkly pricing scales badly at your stage
  - Unleash runs cleanly on Render, uses Postgres natively
```

---

## The Case Against Each Alternative

### ❌ Build It Yourself

The obvious problems aren't the obvious ones:

```typescript
// You'll start with this (day 1)
const flags = { newCheckout: true };

// Then you'll need targeting (day 3)
// Then you'll need percentage rollouts (day 5)
// Then you'll need audit logs (day 8)
// Then a kill switch UI (day 10)
// Then cache invalidation (day 12)
// Then you'll need it to work on the Edge (day 14)
// Then you'll still be building it (day 20)
```

**The real cost is not 2 weeks — it's forever.**
Someone on your 4-person team now owns this system.

### ❌ LaunchDarkly

Good product. Genuinely hard to recommend at early stage:
- Pricing is per-seat + per-MAU, gets expensive fast
- You're paying for enterprise features you won't use
- Vendor lock-in on a non-critical system
- Budget pressure will make you *hesitate to use flags* — defeating the purpose

---

## Concrete Setup: Unleash on Render + Vercel

### 1. Deploy Unleash Server on Render

```yaml
# render.yaml
services:
  - type: web
    name: unleash
    env: docker
    dockerfilePath: ./Dockerfile.unleash  # or use their official image
    envVars:
      - key: DATABASE_URL
        fromDatabase:
          name: unleash-db
          property: connectionString
      - key: INIT_ADMIN_API_TOKENS
        value: your-secret-token

databases:
  - name: unleash-db
    plan: starter  # $7/mo, fine to start
```

Or just use Unleash's official Docker image directly on Render — no custom Dockerfile needed:

```
Image: unleashorg/unleash-server:latest
```

### 2. TypeScript Backend Integration (Render service)

```typescript
// lib/featureFlags.ts
import { initialize, isEnabled, getVariant } from 'unleash-client';

const unleash = initialize({
  url: process.env.UNLEASH_URL!,
  appName: 'my-backend',
  customHeaders: {
    Authorization: process.env.UNLEASH_API_TOKEN!,
  },
  // Polls every 15s by default — fine for most cases
});

// Wait for initial flag sync before handling requests
export async function waitForFlags(): Promise<void> {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    unleash.on('synchronized', resolve);
    // Don't hang forever
    setTimeout(resolve, 3000);
  });
}

// Typed wrapper — don't scatter raw SDK calls everywhere
export const flags = {
  newCheckout: (userId?: string) =>
    isEnabled('new-checkout', userId ? { userId } : undefined),

  betaSearch: (userId?: string) =>
    isEnabled('beta-search', userId ? { userId } : undefined),

  checkoutVariant: (userId: string) =>
    getVariant('checkout-experiment', { userId }),
} as const;
```

```typescript
// server.ts
import { waitForFlags } from './lib/featureFlags';

async function start() {
  await waitForFlags(); // Flags ready before first request
  app.listen(3000);
}
```

### 3. Vercel Edge / API Routes

```typescript
// The Node SDK won't work on Edge runtime — use HTTP API directly
// lib/featureFlags.edge.ts

interface FlagContext {
  userId?: string;
  sessionId?: string;
}

// Cache at the request level (or use Vercel KV for cross-request caching)
async function getFlagsForContext(context: FlagContext) {
  const res = await fetch(
    `${process.env.UNLEASH_URL}/api/client/features`,
    {
      headers: {
        Authorization: process.env.UNLEASH_API_TOKEN!,
      },
      // Vercel fetch cache — revalidate every 30s
      next: { revalidate: 30 },
    }
  );

  const { features } = await res.json();
  return features;
}

export async function isFlagEnabled(
  flagName: string,
  context: FlagContext
): Promise<boolean> {
  try {
    const features = await getFlagsForContext(context);
    const flag = features.find((f: any) => f.name === flagName);
    return flag?.enabled ?? false; // Fail closed
  } catch {
    return false; // Always fail closed on errors
  }
}
```

### 4. Usage Pattern in API Routes

```typescript
// pages/api/checkout.ts  (or app/api/checkout/route.ts)
import { flags } from '../../lib/featureFlags';

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { userId } = await getSession(req);

  if (flags.newCheckout(userId)) {
    return newCheckoutHandler(req);
  }

  return legacyCheckoutHandler(req);
}
```

---

## Operational Guardrails

### Flag Naming Convention (agree on this day 1)

```
{area}-{description}-{type}

new-checkout-flow-rollout      ✅
beta-search-experiment         ✅
disable-email-notifications    ✅ (kill switch)

newcheckout                    ❌ (unclear)
flag1                          ❌ (obviously bad)
```

### Flag Lifecycle — Don't Skip This

```typescript
// Add to your PR template:
/**
 * Feature: New Checkout Flow
 * Flag: new-checkout-flow-rollout
 * Owner: @alice
 * Cleanup by: 2024-03-01  <-- hard date, not "when stable"
 *
 * Rollout:
 *  [ ] 5%  internal users
 *  [ ] 20% beta users
 *  [ ] 100% — flag removal PR due
 */
```

Flags that never get cleaned up become **hidden conditionals** in your codebase.
Schedule the removal PR when you create the flag.

### What to Put Behind Flags (and What Not To)

```
Good candidates:
✅ UI redesigns during gradual rollout
✅ New algorithms (ranking, pricing, search)
✅ Third-party integrations (can kill-switch if they go down)
✅ Expensive features (rate-limit by enabling for paid users only)
✅ Anything you're not confident about

Bad candidates:
❌ Security controls (these should always be on)
❌ Bug fixes (just ship them)
❌ Permanent configuration (use env vars instead)
```

---

## Decision Summary

```
Week 1:  Spin up Unleash on Render         (~3 hours)
Week 1:  Add SDK to backend, write wrapper (~2 hours)
Week 1:  Add edge-compatible fetch client  (~1 hour)
Week 1:  Document naming + lifecycle rules (~1 hour)

Total: ~1 day
